Package io.brane.core.model

Record Class TransactionRequest

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
io.brane.core.model.TransactionRequest
Record Components:
from - the address sending the transaction (required)
to - the recipient address, or null for contract deployment
value - the amount of native currency to transfer, or null for zero
gasLimit - the maximum gas to use, or null to auto-estimate
gasPrice - the gas price for legacy transactions, or null
maxPriorityFeePerGas - the miner tip for EIP-1559 transactions, or null
maxFeePerGas - the maximum total fee for EIP-1559 transactions, or null
nonce - the transaction nonce, or null to auto-fetch
data - the transaction input data (calldata), or null for simple transfers
isEip1559 - true for EIP-1559 transactions, false for legacy
accessList - the EIP-2930 access list, or null/empty
public record TransactionRequest(Address from, Address to, Wei value, Long gasLimit, Wei gasPrice, Wei maxPriorityFeePerGas, Wei maxFeePerGas, Long nonce, HexData data, boolean isEip1559, List<AccessListEntry> accessList) extends Record
Request to submit a transaction to the blockchain.

This type supports both legacy and EIP-1559 transaction types:

  • Legacy transactions (isEip1559 = false): Use gasPrice
  • EIP-1559 transactions (isEip1559 = true): Use maxFeePerGas and maxPriorityFeePerGas

Optional vs Required Fields:

  • Required: from (sender address)
  • Optional: All other fields can be null and will be auto-filled by WalletClient:
    • gasLimit - estimated via eth_estimateGas if null
    • nonce - fetched from eth_getTransactionCount if null
    • gasPrice/maxFeePerGas - fetched from network if null

Contract Interaction:

  • Contract call: Set to to contract address, data to encoded function call
  • Contract deployment: Set to to null, data to bytecode + constructor args
  • Simple transfer: Set to to recipient, value to amount, data can be null/empty
